11muggH::muggH(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
12: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
13{
14 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
15 throw std::runtime_error("muggH called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
16}
17
18double muggH::computeThValue()
19{
20 return myNPbase->muggH(sqrt_s);
21}

669: ThObservable(SM_i)

672 throw std::runtime_error("BrHto2e2vRatio called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
673}
674
675double BrHto2e2vRatio::computeThValue()
676{
677 // SM decay widths (from MG simulations)
678 double wH2e2vSM=0.93291e-06, wH2evSM=0.10152e-04;
679
680 // Sum
681 double wH2e2vTSM=wH2e2vSM+wH2evSM;
682
683 return ( (wH2e2vSM*(myNPbase->BrH2e2vRatio()) + wH2evSM*(myNPbase->BrH2evRatio())) / wH2e2vTSM );
684}

701

703}

1106
1107
1108// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1109// Full signal strengths (prod x decay)
1110// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1111
1112muggHgaga::muggHgaga(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1113: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1114{
1115 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1116 throw std::runtime_error("muggHgaga called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1117}
1118
1119double muggHgaga::computeThValue()
1120{
1121 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1122 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1123 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1124 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muggH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio()));
1125 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muggH_1(sqrt_s);
1126 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muggH_2(sqrt_s);
1127 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio1();
1128 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio2();
1129
1130 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1131 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1132 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1133 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1134 return ( 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1) );
1135 } else {
1136 return myNPbase->muggHgaga(sqrt_s);
1137 }
1138}
1139
1140muggHgagaInt::muggHgagaInt(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1141: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1142{
1143 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1144 throw std::runtime_error("muggHgagaInt called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1145}
1146
1147double muggHgagaInt::computeThValue()
1148{
1149 return (myNPbase->muggHgagaInt(sqrt_s)) / (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
1150}
1151
1152muVBFHgaga::muVBFHgaga(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1153: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1154{
1155 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1156 throw std::runtime_error("muVBFHgaga called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1157}
1158
1159double muVBFHgaga::computeThValue()
1160{
1161 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1162 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1163 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1164 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muVBF(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio()));
1165 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muVBF_1(sqrt_s);
1166 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muVBF_2(sqrt_s);
1167 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio1();
1168 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio2();
1169
1170 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1171 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1172 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1173 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1174
1175 double mu;
1176
1177 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1178
1179 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1180
1181 return mu;
1182 } else {
1183 return myNPbase->muVBFHgaga(sqrt_s);
1184 }
1185}
1186
1187muZHgaga::muZHgaga(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1188: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1189{
1190 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1191 throw std::runtime_error("muZHgaga called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1192}
1193
1194double muZHgaga::computeThValue()
1195{
1196 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1197 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1198 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1199 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muZH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio()));
1200 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muZH_1(sqrt_s);
1201 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muZH_2(sqrt_s);
1202 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio1();
1203 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio2();
1204
1205 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1206 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1207 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1208 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1209
1210 double mu;
1211
1212 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1213
1214 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1215
1216 return mu;
1217
1218 } else {
1219 return myNPbase->muZHgaga(sqrt_s);
1220 }
1221}

1317
1318double mutHgaga::computeThValue()
1319{
1320 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1321 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1322 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1323 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_mutH_1(sqrt_s);
1324 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_mutH_2(sqrt_s);
1325 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio1();
1326 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio2();
1327
1328 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1329 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1330 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1331 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1332
1333 double mu;
1334
1335 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1336
1337 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1338
1339 return mu;
1340
1341 } else {
1342 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
1343 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
1344 double NPmutHgaga = myNPbase->mutHgaga(sqrt_s);
1345 if(NPmutHgaga==1.0){
1346 return ((myNPbase->mutH(sqrt_s)) )*(myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
1347 } else{
1348 return NPmutHgaga;
1349 }
1350 }
1351}

1399{

1401 throw std::runtime_error("muttHptH_Hgaga called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1402}
1403
1404double muttHptH_Hgaga::computeThValue() //AG:added
1405{
1406 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
1407 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
1408 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
1409 //check this.
1410 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
1411 double xsSM_ttH = 0.499873;
1412 double xsSM_tH = 0.0821;
1413 //double xsSM_ttH = myNPbase->computeSigmattH(sqrt_s);
1414 //double xsSM_tH = myNPbase->computeSigmatHq(sqrt_s);
1415
1416 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1417 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1418 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1419 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
1420 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
1421 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio1();
1422 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHgagaRatio2();
1423
1424 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1425 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1426 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1427 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1428
1429 double mu;
1430
1431 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1432
1433 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1434
1435 return mu;
1436
1437 } else {
1438 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
1439 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
1440 double NPmuttHptH_Hgaga = myNPbase->muttHptH_Hgaga(sqrt_s);
1441 if(NPmuttHptH_Hgaga==1.0){
1442 return ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->muttH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->mutH(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) * (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio()) ;
1443 } else {
1444 return NPmuttHptH_Hgaga;
1445 }
1446 }
1447}

1698 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1699
1700 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1701
1702 return mu;
1703
1704 } else {
1705 return myNPbase->muZHZZ(sqrt_s);
1706 }
1707}

1709muWHZZ::muWHZZ(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1710: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1711{
1712 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1713 throw std::runtime_error("muWHZZ called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1714}
1715
1716double muWHZZ::computeThValue()
1717{
1718 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1719 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muWH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio()));
1720 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1721 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1722 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muWH_1(sqrt_s);
1723 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muWH_2(sqrt_s);
1724 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHZZRatio1();
1725 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHZZRatio2();
1726
1727 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1728 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1729 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1730 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1731
1732 double mu;
1733
1734 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1735
1736 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1737
1738 return mu;
1739
1740 } else {
1741 return myNPbase->muWHZZ(sqrt_s);
1742 }
1743}

1745muVHZZ::muVHZZ(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i)
1746: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
1747{
1748 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
1749 throw std::runtime_error("muVHZZ called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
1750}
1751
1752double muVHZZ::computeThValue()
1753{
1754 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
1755 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
1756 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
1757 //check this.
1758 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
1759 double xsSM_WH = 1.21539;
1760 double xsSM_ZH = 0.795910;
1761 //double xsSM_WH = myNPbase->computeSigmaWH(sqrt_s);
1762 //double xsSM_ZH = myNPbase->computeSigmaZH(sqrt_s);
1763 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
1764 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
1765 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
1766 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muVH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio()));
1767 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH);
1768 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH);
1769 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHZZRatio1();
1770 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHZZRatio2();
1771
1772 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
1773 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
1774 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
1775 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
1776
1777 double mu;
1778
1779 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
1780
1781 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
1782
1783 return mu;
1784
1785 } else {
1786 //return myNPbase->muVHZZ(sqrt_s);
1787 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
1788 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
1789 double NPmuVHZZ = myNPbase->muVHZZ(sqrt_s);
1790 if(NPmuVHZZ==1.0){
1791 return ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->muZH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->muWH(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH) * (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
1792 } else {
1793 return NPmuVHZZ;
1794 }
1795 }
1796}

2190}
2191
2192double muWHWW::computeThValue()
2193{
2194 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
2195 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
2196 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
2197 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muWH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio()));
2198 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muWH_1(sqrt_s);
2199 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muWH_2(sqrt_s);
2200 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHWWRatio1();
2201 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHWWRatio2();
2202
2203 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
2204 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
2205 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
2206 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
2207
2208 double mu;
2209
2210 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
2211
2212 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
2213
2214 return mu;
2215
2216 } else {
2217 return myNPbase->muWHWW(sqrt_s);
2218 }
2219}

2260double muttHptH_HWW::computeThValue() //AG:added
2261{
2262
2263 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
2264 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
2265 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
2266 //check this.
2267 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
2268 double xsSM_ttH = 0.499873;
2269 double xsSM_tH = 0.0821;
2270 //double xsSM_ttH = myNPbase->computeSigmattH(sqrt_s);
2271 //double xsSM_tH = myNPbase->computeSigmatHq(sqrt_s);
2272 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
2273 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
2274 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
2275 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
2276 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
2277 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHWWRatio1();
2278 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHWWRatio2();
2279
2280 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
2281 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
2282 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
2283 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
2284
2285 double mu;
2286
2287 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
2288
2289 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
2290
2291 return mu;
2292
2293 } else {
2294
2295 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
2296 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
2297 double NPmuttHptH_HWW = myNPbase->muttHptH_HWW(sqrt_s);
2298 if(NPmuttHptH_HWW==1.0){
2299 return ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->muttH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->mutH(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) * (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio()) ;
2300 } else {
2301 return NPmuttHptH_HWW;
2302 }
2303 }
2304}

2594double muVHmumu::computeThValue()
2595{
2596
2597 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
2598 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
2599 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
2600 //check this.
2601 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
2602 double xsSM_WH = 1.21539;
2603 double xsSM_ZH = 0.795910;
2604 //double xsSM_WH = myNPbase->computeSigmaWH(sqrt_s);
2605 //double xsSM_ZH = myNPbase->computeSigmaZH(sqrt_s);
2606 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
2607 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muVH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHmumuRatio()));
2608 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
2609 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
2610 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH);
2611 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH);
2612 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio1();
2613 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio2();
2614
2615 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
2616 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
2617 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
2618 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
2619
2620 double mu;
2621
2622 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
2623
2624 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
2625
2626 return mu;
2627
2628 } else {
2629 //return myNPbase->muVHmumu(sqrt_s);
2630 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
2631 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
2632 double NPmuVHmumu = myNPbase->muVHmumu(sqrt_s);
2633 if(NPmuVHmumu==1.0){
2634 return ( xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->muZH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->muWH(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ZH+xsSM_WH) * (myNPbase->BrHmumuRatio());
2635 } else {

2658muggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu::muggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i) //AG:added
2659: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
2660{
2661 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
2662 throw std::runtime_error("muggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
2663}
2664
2665double muggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu::computeThValue() //AG:added
2666{
2667 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
2668 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
2669 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
2670 //check this. Furthermore, the bbH is not included. In the SM this is
2671 //very suppressed (and it's probably also the case in the SMEFT) but
2672 //in some NP models it may not be the case.Unfortunately, bbH is not
2673 //obtained in the SMEFT, we could just set delta_mubbH to zero in the
2674 //SMEFT and add here the general expression.
2675 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
2676 double xsSM_ggHbbH = 44.745;
2677 double xsSM_ttH = 0.4998;
2678 double xsSM_tH = 0.084769;
2679 //double xsSM_ggH = myNPbase->computeSigmaggH(sqrt_s);
2680 //double xsSM_ttH = myNPbase->computeSigmattH(sqrt_s);
2681 //double xsSM_tH = myNPbase->computeSigmatH(sqrt_s);
2682 //double xsSM_bbH = myNPbase->computeSigmabbH(sqrt_s);
2683
2684
2685
2686 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
2687 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
2688 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
2689 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->delta_muggH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) ;
2690 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->delta_muggH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) ;
2691 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio1();
2692 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio2();
2693
2694 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
2695 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
2696 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
2697 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
2698
2699 double mu;
2700
2701 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
2702
2703 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
2704
2705 return mu;
2706
2707 } else {
2708
2709 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
2710 //(which is the observable we fit at the end). Furthermore, the Hbb
2711 //is not added in the original formula, fine for the SM (probably also
2712 //for the SMEFT) but not for all NP models.
2713 double NPmuggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu = myNPbase->muggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu(sqrt_s);
2714 if(NPmuggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu==1.0){
2715 return ( (xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->muggH(sqrt_s))+xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->muttH(sqrt_s))+xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->mutH(sqrt_s))) / (xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) )*(myNPbase->BrHmumuRatio()) ;
2716 } else {
2717 return NPmuggHpttHptHpbbH_Hmumu;
2718 }
2719 }
2720}

2729double muVBFpVH_Hmumu::computeThValue() //AG:added
2730{
2731
2732 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
2733 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
2734 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
2735 //check this.
2736 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
2737 double xsSM_VBF = 3.49948;
2738 double xsSM_WH = 1.21539;
2739 double xsSM_ZH = 0.795910;
2740 //double xsSM_VBF = myNPbase->computeSigmaVBF(sqrt_s);
2741 //double xsSM_WH = myNPbase->computeSigmaWH(sqrt_s);
2742 //double xsSM_ZH = myNPbase->computeSigmaZH(sqrt_s);
2743 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
2744 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
2745 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
2746 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->delta_muVBF_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_VBF+xsSM_WH+xsSM_ZH);
2747 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->delta_muVBF_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->delta_muWH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->delta_muZH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_VBF+xsSM_WH+xsSM_ZH);
2748 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio1();
2749 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHmumuRatio2();
2750
2751 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
2752 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
2753 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
2754 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
2755
2756 double mu;
2757
2758 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
2759
2760 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
2761
2762 return mu;
2763
2764 } else {
2765
2766 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
2767 //(which is the observable we fit at the end).
2768 double NPmuVBFpVH_Hmumu = myNPbase->muVBFpVH_Hmumu(sqrt_s);
2769 if(NPmuVBFpVH_Hmumu==1.0){
2770 return ( (xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->muVBF(sqrt_s))+xsSM_WH*(myNPbase->muWH(sqrt_s))+xsSM_ZH*(myNPbase->muZH(sqrt_s))) / (xsSM_VBF+xsSM_WH+xsSM_ZH) )*(myNPbase->BrHmumuRatio()) ;
2771 } else {
2772 return NPmuVBFpVH_Hmumu;
2773 }
2774 }

3130 //return ( -1.0 + (myNPbase->muggH(sqrt_s)) + (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio()));
3131 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
3132 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
3133 double muProd1 = myNPbase->delta_muggH_1(sqrt_s);
3134 double muProd2 = myNPbase->delta_muggH_2(sqrt_s);
3135 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio1();
3136 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio2();
3137
3138 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
3139 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
3140 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
3141 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
3142
3143 double mu;
3144
3145 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
3146
3147 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
3148
3149 return mu;
3150
3151 } else {
3152 return myNPbase->muggHbb(sqrt_s);
3153 }
3154}

3276muttHptH_Hbb::muttHptH_Hbb(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i) //AG:added
3277: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
3278{
3279 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
3280 throw std::runtime_error("muttHptH_Hbb called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
3281}
3282
3283double muttHptH_Hbb::computeThValue() //AG:added
3284{
3285 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
3286 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
3287 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
3288 //check this.
3289 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
3290 double xsSM_ttH = 0.499873;
3291 double xsSM_tH = 0.0821;
3292 //double xsSM_ttH = myNPbase->computeSigmattH(sqrt_s);
3293 //double xsSM_tH = myNPbase->computeSigmatHq(sqrt_s);
3294 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
3295 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
3296 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
3297 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
3298 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->delta_muttH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->delta_mutH_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH);
3299 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio1();
3300 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio2();
3301
3302 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
3303 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
3304 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
3305 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
3306
3307 double mu;
3308
3309 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
3310
3311 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
3312
3313 return mu;
3314
3315 } else {
3316
3317
3318 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
3319 //(which is the observable we fit at the end)
3320 double NPmuttHptH_Hbb = myNPbase->muttHptH_Hbb(sqrt_s);
3321 if(NPmuttHptH_Hbb==1.0){
3322 return ( xsSM_ttH*(myNPbase->muttH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_tH*(myNPbase->mutH(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ttH+xsSM_tH) * (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio()) ;
3323 } else {
3324 return NPmuttHptH_Hbb;
3325 }
3326 }
3327}

3329muggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb::muggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i) //AG:added
3330: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i)
3331{
3332 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
3333 throw std::runtime_error("muggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
3334}
3335
3336double muggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb::computeThValue() //AG:added
3337{
3338 //VM:Note that these values are valid for 13 TeV, they are not general
3339 //We should access the SM function that has all the values (for the
3340 //different energies). The values are slightly different, we should
3341 //check this. Furthermore, the bbH is not included. In the SM this is
3342 //very suppressed (and it's probably also the case in the SMEFT) but
3343 //in some NP models it may not be the case.Unfortunately, bbH is not
3344 //obtained in the SMEFT, we could just set delta_mubbH to zero in the
3345 //SMEFT and add here the general expression.
3346 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure2a (symmetrized)
3347 double xsSM_ggHbbH = 44.745;
3348 double xsSM_VBF = 3.49948;
3349 //double xsSM_ggH = myNPbase->computeSigmaggH(sqrt_s);
3350 //double xsSM_VBF = myNPbase->computeSigmaVBF(sqrt_s);
3351 //double xsSM_bbH = myNPbase->computeSigmabbH(sqrt_s);
3352 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized() || (this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()) {
3353 //AG: Most general expression including quadratic corrections.
3354 // If FlagQuadraticTerms=false, the quadratic pieces become 0 in NPSMEFTd6General
3355 double muProd1 = ( xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->delta_muggH_1(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->delta_muVBF_1(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_VBF);
3356 double muProd2 = ( xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->delta_muggH_2(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->delta_muVBF_2(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_VBF);
3357 double dGammaR1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio1();
3358 double dGammaR2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaHbbRatio2();
3359
3360 double dGammaRTot1 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio1();
3361 double dGammaRTot2 = myNPbase->deltaGammaTotalRatio2();
3362 double Br1 = dGammaR1-dGammaRTot1;
3363 double Br2 = dGammaR2 -dGammaRTot2 - dGammaR1*dGammaRTot1 + pow(dGammaRTot1,2.0);
3364
3365 double mu;
3366
3367 mu = 1.0 + (muProd1 + Br1) + (muProd2 + Br2 + muProd1*Br1);
3368
3369 if (mu < 0) return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
3370
3371 return mu;
3372
3373 } else {
3374
3375
3376 //VM: Just in case someone wants to add directly the production*decay
3377 //(which is the observable we fit at the end). Furthermore, the Hbb
3378 //is not added in the original formula, fine for the SM (probably also
3379 //for the SMEFT) but not for all NP models.
3380 double NPmuggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb = myNPbase->muggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb(sqrt_s);
3381 if(NPmuggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb==1.0){
3382 return ( xsSM_ggHbbH*(myNPbase->muggH(sqrt_s)) + xsSM_VBF*(myNPbase->muVBF(sqrt_s)) )/(xsSM_ggHbbH+xsSM_VBF) * (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio()) ;
3383 } else {
3384 return NPmuggHpVBFpbbH_Hbb;
3385 }
3386 }
3387}

4008{

4014{

4017 } else {
4018 return (myNPbase->mueeZH(sqrt_s, Pol_em, Pol_ep))*(myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
4019 }

6957STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0::STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i, unsigned int fstate_i)
6958: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i), fstate(fstate_i)
6959{
6960 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
6961 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0 called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
6962
6963}
6964
6965double STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0::computeThValue()
6966{
6967 //-- Production:
6968 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
6969
6970 double muProd = myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0(sqrt_s);
6971 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
6972 double muProd2 = 0.0;
6973 //-- Decay:
6974 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
6975 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
6976 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
6977
6978 if (fstate == 1){
6979 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
6980 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
6981 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
6982 } else if (fstate == 2){
6983 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHgagaRatio());
6984 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
6985 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
6986 } else if (fstate == 3){
6987 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHbbRatio());
6988 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
6989 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
6990 } else if (fstate == 4){
6991 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
6992 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
6993 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
6994 } else {
6995 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH10_Inf_Nj0 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
6996 }
6997
6998 //-- Production x Decay:
6999 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
7000 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
7001 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
7002 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
7003 } else {
7004 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7005 }
7006}

7020
7021}
7022
7023double STXS12_ggH_pTH0_10_Nj0::computeThValue()
7024{
7025 //-- Production:
7026 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
7027 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
7028 double muProd = myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_pTH0_10_Nj0(sqrt_s);
7029 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
7030 double muProd2 = 0.0;
7031
7032 //-- Decay:
7033 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
7034 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
7035 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7036 if (fstate==0){
7037 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
7038 weight = (6.6369); //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
7039 } else if (fstate == 1){
7040 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
7041 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7042 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7043 } else if (fstate == 2){
7044 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
7045 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7046 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7047 } else if (fstate == 3){
7048 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
7049 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7050 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7051 } else if (fstate == 4){
7052 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
7053 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7054 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7055 } else if (fstate == 5){
7056 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
7057 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7058 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7059 } else if (fstate == 6){
7060 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
7061 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7062 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7063 } else if (fstate == 7){
7064 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
7065 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7066 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7067 } else {
7068 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH0_10_Nj0 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
7069 }
7070
7071 //-- Production x Decay:
7072 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
7073 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
7074 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
7075 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
7076 } else {
7077 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7078 }
7079
7080}

7172 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
7173 double muProd = ( 6.6369*(myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_pTH0_10_Nj0(sqrt_s)) +
7174 20.642*(myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_pTH10_200_Nj0(sqrt_s)) )
7175 /(6.6369 + 20.642);
7176 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
7177 double muProd2 = 0.0;
7178
7179 //-- Decay:
7180 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
7181 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
7182 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7183 if (fstate==0){
7184 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
7185 weight = (6.6369 + 20.642); //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
7186 } else if (fstate == 1){
7187 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
7188 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7189 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7190 } else if (fstate == 2){
7191 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
7192 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7193 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7194 } else if (fstate == 3){
7195 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
7196 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7197 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7198 } else if (fstate == 4){
7199 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
7200 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7201 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7202 } else if (fstate == 5){
7203 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
7204 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7205 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7206 } else if (fstate == 6){
7207 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
7208 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7209 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7210 } else if (fstate == 7){
7211 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
7212 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7213 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7214 } else {
7215 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH0_200_Nj0 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
7216 }
7217
7218 //-- Production x Decay:
7219 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
7220 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
7221 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
7222 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
7223 } else {
7224 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7225 }

7654 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7655 }

7666: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i), fstate(fstate_i)

7672
7673double STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH120_200_Nj2::computeThValue() //AG:modified
7674{
7675 //-- Production:
7676 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
7677 double muProd = myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH120_200_Nj2(sqrt_s);
7678 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
7679 double muProd2 = 0.0;
7680
7681 //-- Decay:
7682 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
7683 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
7684 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7685 if (fstate==0){
7686 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
7687 weight = 0.94325; //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
7688 } else if (fstate == 1){
7689 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
7690 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7691 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7692 } else if (fstate == 2){
7693 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
7694 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7695 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7696 } else if (fstate == 3){
7697 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
7698 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7699 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7700 } else if (fstate == 4){
7701 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
7702 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7703 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7704 } else if (fstate == 5){
7705 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
7706 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7707 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7708 }else {
7709 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH120_200_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
7710 }
7711
7712 //-- Production x Decay:
7713 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
7714 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
7715 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
7716 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
7717 } else {
7718 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7719 }
7720
7721}

7735double STXS12_ggH_mjj350_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2::computeThValue()
7736{
7737 //-- Production:
7738 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
7739 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
7740 //We should weight each xsection with the SM prediction. We need to check
7741 //this values, nevertheless, the difference between the two parametrisations
7742 //is extremely small (way beyond our current precision)
7743 double muProd = ((myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)) +
7744 (myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj700_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)) )
7745 /(2.);
7746 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
7747 double muProd2 = 0.0;
7748
7749 //-- Decay:
7750 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
7751 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
7752 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7753 if (fstate==0){
7754 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
7755 weight = (0.92136); //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
7756 } else if (fstate == 1){
7757 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
7758 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7759 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7760 } else if (fstate == 2){
7761 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
7762 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7763 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7764 } else if (fstate == 3){
7765 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
7766 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7767 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7768 } else if (fstate == 4){
7769 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
7770 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7771 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7772 } else if (fstate == 5){
7773 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
7774 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7775 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7776 } else if (fstate == 6){
7777 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
7778 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7779 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7780 } else if (fstate == 7){
7781 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
7782 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7783 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7784 } else {
7785 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_mjj350_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
7786 }
7787
7788 //-- Production x Decay:
7789 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
7790 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
7791 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
7792 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
7793 } else {
7794 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
7795 }
7796

7938{

7944double STXS12_ggH_pTH0_200_Nj2::computeThValue()
7945{
7946
7947
7948

7950 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
7951 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
7952 //VM: In the reference above we have the SM predictions for less bins. Angelica should have
7953 //the ones for Madgraph and we could use those. In any case the parametrisation is very stable
7954 //we give the same weight to the bins for which we don't have the SM prediction (for the moment)!
7955 //The possible error that we could be introducing here is way below our precision!
7956 double muProd = (
7957 2.9636/2*(myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH0_60_Nj2(sqrt_s)+myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH60_120_Nj2(sqrt_s))+
7958 0.94321*(myNPbase->STXS12_ggH_mjj0_350_pTH120_200_Nj2(sqrt_s))+

7960 )/(2.9636+0.94321+0.87751);
7961 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
7962 double muProd2 = 0.0;
7963
7964 //-- Decay:
7965 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
7966 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
7967 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7968 if (fstate==0){
7969 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
7970 weight = (2.9636+0.94321+0.87751); //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
7971 } else if (fstate == 1){
7972 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
7973 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7974 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7975 } else if (fstate == 2){
7976 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
7977 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7978 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7979 } else if (fstate == 3){
7980 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
7981 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7982 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7983 } else if (fstate == 4){

7985 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7986 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7987 } else if (fstate == 5){
7988 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
7989 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7990 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7991 } else if (fstate == 6){
7992 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
7993 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7994 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7995 } else if (fstate == 7){
7996 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
7997 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
7998 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
7999 } else {
8000 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH0_200_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");

8798STXS12_qqHqq_VH_veto_Nj01::STXS12_qqHqq_VH_veto_Nj01(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i, unsigned int fstate_i)
8799: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i), fstate(fstate_i)
8800{
8801 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
8802 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_VH_veto_Nj01 called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
8803
8804}
8805
8806double STXS12_qqHqq_VH_veto_Nj01::computeThValue()
8807{
8808 //-- Production:
8809 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
8810 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
8811 double muProd = myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_VH_veto_Nj01(sqrt_s);
8812 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
8813 double muProd2 = 0.0;
8814
8815 //-- Decay:
8816 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
8817 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
8818 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8819 if (fstate==0){
8820 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
8821 weight = (1.); //Not available in Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
8822 } else if (fstate == 1){
8823 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
8824 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8825 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8826 } else if (fstate == 2){
8827 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
8828 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8829 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8830 } else if (fstate == 3){
8831 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
8832 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8833 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8834 } else if (fstate == 4){
8835 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
8836 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8837 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8838 } else if (fstate == 5){
8839 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
8840 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8841 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8842 } else if (fstate == 6){
8843 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
8844 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8845 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8846 } else if (fstate == 7){
8847 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
8848 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
8849 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
8850 } else {
8851 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ggH_pTH200_300 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
8852 }
8853
8854 //-- Production x Decay:
8855 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
8856 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
8857 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
8858 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
8859 } else {
8860 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
8861 }
8862
8863}

9242STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2::STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i, unsigned int fstate_i) //AG:added
9243: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i), fstate(fstate_i)
9244{
9245 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
9246 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2 called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
9247
9248}
9249
9250double STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2::computeThValue() //AG:added
9251{
9252 //-- Production:
9253 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
9254 double muProd = myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s) ;
9255 double muProd1 = muProd -1.0;
9256 double muProd2 = 0.0;
9257
9258 //-- Decay:
9259 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
9260 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
9261 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9262 if (fstate==0){
9263 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
9264 weight = 0.53537; //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
9265 } else if (fstate == 1){
9266 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
9267 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9268 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9269 } else if (fstate == 2){
9270 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
9271 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9272 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9273 } else if (fstate == 3){
9274 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
9275 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9276 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9277 } else if (fstate == 4){
9278 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
9279 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9280 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9281 } else if (fstate == 5){
9282 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
9283 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9284 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9285 } else if (fstate == 6){
9286 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
9287 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9288 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9289 } else {
9290 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
9291 }
9292
9293 //-- Production x Decay:
9294 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
9295 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
9296 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
9297 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
9298 } else {
9299 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
9300 }
9301
9302
9303}

9514{
9515 //-- Production:
9516 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
9517 //Since adding bins, include partial weigths of SM_predictions
9518 //(https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.)
9519 double muProd = (0.22408*(myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1000_1500_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s))
9520 + 0.21578*(myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1500_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)) / (0.30189+0.21578));
9521 double muProd1 = (0.22408*(myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1000_1500_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)-1.0)
9522 + 0.21578*(myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1500_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)-1.0) / (0.30189+0.21578));
9523 double muProd2 = 0.0;
9524
9525 //-- Decay:
9526 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
9527 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
9528 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9529 if (fstate==0){
9530 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
9531 weight = 1.0 ; //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
9532 } else if (fstate == 1){
9533 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
9534 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9535 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9536 } else if (fstate == 2){
9537 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
9538 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9539 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9540 } else if (fstate == 3){
9541 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
9542 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9543 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9544 } else if (fstate == 4){
9545 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
9546 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9547 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9548 } else {
9549 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1000_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
9550 }
9551
9552 //-- Production x Decay:
9553 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
9554 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
9555 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
9556 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );

9682STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_Inf_Nj2::STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_Inf_Nj2(const StandardModel& SM_i, const double sqrt_s_i, unsigned int fstate_i) //AG:added
9683: ThObservable(SM_i), sqrt_s(sqrt_s_i), fstate(fstate_i)
9684{
9685 if ((myNPbase = dynamic_cast<const NPbase*> (&SM)) == NULL)
9686 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_Inf_Nj2 called with a class whose parent is not NPbase");
9687
9688}
9689
9690double STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_Inf_Nj2::computeThValue() //AG:added
9691{
9692 //-- Production:
9693 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
9694 //Since adding bins, include partial weigths of SM_predictions
9695 //(https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.)
9696
9697 double muProd = (0.53537*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_700_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)
9698 + 0.25614*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj700_1000_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)
9699 + 0.22408*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1000_1500_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)
9700 + 0.21578*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1500_Inf_pTH0_200_Nj2(sqrt_s)
9701 + 0.073727*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_1000_pTH200_Inf_Nj2(sqrt_s)
9702 + 0.07315*myNPbase->STXS12_qqHqq_mjj1000_Inf_pTH200_Inf_Nj2(sqrt_s))
9703 / (0.53537+0.25614+0.22408+0.21578+0.073727+0.07315) ;
9704
9705 double muProd1 = muProd - 1.;
9706 double muProd2 = 0.0;
9707
9708 //-- Decay:
9709 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
9710 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
9711 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9712 if (fstate==0){
9713 // Use for Cross-section [pb] with no Higgs-boson decay
9714 weight = (0.53537+0.25614+0.22408+0.21578+0.073727+0.07315); //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7.
9715 } else if (fstate == 1){
9716 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
9717 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9718 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9719 } else if (fstate == 2){
9720 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
9721 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9722 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9723 } else if (fstate == 3){
9724 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
9725 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9726 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9727 } else if (fstate == 4){
9728 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
9729 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9730 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9731 } else if (fstate == 5){
9732 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
9733 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
9734 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
9735 } else {
9736 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_qqHqq_mjj350_Inf_Nj2 called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
9737 }
9738
9739
9740
9741
9742 //-- Production x Decay:
9743 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
9744// std::cout<<"\033[1;31m CHECK IF LINEAR \033[0m" << std::endl;
9745 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
9746 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
9747// std::cout<<"\033[1;31m CHECK IF QUADRATIC \033[0m" << std::endl;
9748 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
9749 } else {
9750// std::cout<<"\033[1;31m CHECK IF NEITHER LINEAR NOR QUADRATIC \033[0m" << std::endl;
9751 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
9752 }
9753
9754}

10990 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;

10994 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
10995 } else if (fstate == 4){

10997 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
10998 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
10999 } else {

11001 }

11293 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;

11325double STXS12_ttH::computeThValue() //AG:added
11326{
11327 //-- Production:
11328 double weight = 1.0; //If normalized to the SM
11329 //Ref: https://www.hepdata.net/record/ins2104706 Figure7. After symmetrizing.
11330 //Since adding bins, include partial weigths (SM_predictions)
11331 double muProd = ( 0.09779*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH0_60(sqrt_s)
11332 + 0.13884*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH60_120(sqrt_s)
11333 + 0.05439*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH120_200(sqrt_s)
11334 + 0.05303*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH200_300(sqrt_s)
11335 + 0.00498*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH300_450(sqrt_s)
11336 + 0.00060*myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH450_Inf(sqrt_s) ) /(0.09779 + 0.13884 + 0.05439 + 0.05303 + 0.00498 + 0.00060 );
11337 double muProd1 = ( 0.09779*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH0_60(sqrt_s)-1.0)
11338 + 0.13884*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH60_120(sqrt_s)-1.0)
11339 + 0.05439*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH120_200(sqrt_s)-1.0)
11340 + 0.05303*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH200_300(sqrt_s)-1.0)
11341 + 0.00498*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH300_450(sqrt_s)-1.0)
11342 + 0.00060*(myNPbase->STXS12_ttH_pTH450_Inf(sqrt_s)-1.0) ) /(0.09779 + 0.13884 + 0.05439 + 0.05303 + 0.00498 + 0.00060 );
11343 double muProd2 = 0.0;
11344
11345 //-- Decay:
11346 double BrHXXRatio = 1.0;
11347 double dBrHXXRatio1 = 0.0;
11348 double dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11349 if (fstate==0){
11350 weight = 1.0;
11351 } else if (fstate == 1){
11352 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrH4lRatio());
11353 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11354 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11355 } else if (fstate == 2){
11356 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHgagaRatio());
11357 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11358 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11359 } else if (fstate == 3){
11360 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHbbRatio());
11361 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11362 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11363 } else if (fstate == 4){
11364 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->STXS12_BrHevmuvRatio());
11365 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11366 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11367 } else if (fstate == 5){
11368 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHtautauRatio());
11369 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11370 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11371 } else if (fstate == 6){
11372 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHWWRatio());
11373 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11374 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11375 } else if (fstate == 7){
11376 BrHXXRatio = (myNPbase->BrHZZRatio());
11377 dBrHXXRatio1 = BrHXXRatio - 1.0;
11378 dBrHXXRatio2 = 0.0;
11379 } else {
11380 throw std::runtime_error("STXS12_ttH called with invalid argument for final state in fstate_i");
11381 }
11382
11383 //-- Production x Decay:
11384 if ((this->getModel()).isModelLinearized()){
11385 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1));
11386 } else if((this->getModel()).isModelNPquadratic()){
11387 return weight*( 1.0 + (muProd1 + dBrHXXRatio1) + (muProd2 + dBrHXXRatio2 + muProd1*dBrHXXRatio1) );
11388 } else {
11389 return weight*(muProd)*(BrHXXRatio);
